&lt;h2 id=&quot;what-you-need&quot;&gt;What you need:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Some sort of fire producing apparatus, like a lighter or one of those fancy kitchen blowtorches&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;A big chonky ice cube&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;1 tsp sugar&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;2 oz rye or bourbon. I prefer bourbon because I like my throat to hurt.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;2 dashes orange bitters, or Angostura bitters if that’s what you have&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;1 tsp water&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;A rocks glass&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;2 slices of orange peel
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;do-this&quot;&gt;Do This:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Add sugar, bitters, and water to the rocks glass and stir until sugar is mostly dissolved&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Add the chonky ice cube&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Add the booze and stir gently. It’s had a long day too, you know.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Bend a slice of orange peel so the oils come out and rub on the rim of the glass&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;With your fire maker lit, bend the second slice and bring close to the flame to ignite the ccocktails&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Drop the second slice in the glass&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Drink responsibly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

