&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;what-you-need&quot;&gt;What you need:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;1 29 oz. can crushed tomatoes&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Medium onion, chopped&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;1 or more chopped cloves garlic&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;1 tbsp. crushed red pepper&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;2 tsp. Mexican oregano&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;2 tsp. salt/to taste&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;1 tbsp. ground black pepper&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;4-6 oz. coarsely chopped cilantro&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;1/2-3/4 cup red wine vinegar&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;1/2 cup vegetable oil
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;do-this&quot;&gt;Do This:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Blend all ingredients until smooth&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Refrigerate for at least 8 hours (seriously it improves so much over time)
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mexican oregano is a completely different plant from standard oregano so try to get some if you can.
&lt;br /&gt;
